---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="The Jim Coleman Show Case Study | Dino Favara Jr."
  description="Researched, strategized, and produced a 77x outlier video that gained 80K+ views and 4K subscribers from a single concept."
>
  <Nav />

  <main>
    <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pt-10">
      <a href="/work" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium text-primary/70 hover:text-primary transition-colors duration-200">
        &larr; All case studies
      </a>
    </section>

    <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pt-8 pb-12">
      <span class="inline-block px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-medium bg-purple-500/10 text-purple-700 tracking-wide mb-6">
        Podcast Outlier Strategy
      </span>
      <h1 class="font-display text-[clamp(2rem,5vw,3.2rem)] leading-[1.1] tracking-tight text-dark mb-4">
        The Jim Coleman Show
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg font-light text-dark/60 leading-relaxed max-w-xl">
        Researched, strategized, and produced a 77x outlier video that gained 80K+ views and 4K subscribers from a single concept.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-6">
        {['Audience Research', 'Concept Strategy', 'YouTube Growth', 'Sweet Fish Media'].map(tag => (
          <span class="px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full border border-dark/10 bg-white/60 text-xs font-medium text-dark/55">{tag}</span>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="stats-section max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pb-12">
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-dark/8 bg-white/70 overflow-hidden">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-[1fr_auto_1fr]">
          <div class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center py-10 px-8 text-center">
            <span class="text-[11px] font-medium uppercase tracking-widest text-dark/40 mb-3">Avg Views Before</span>
            <span class="font-display text-[4.5rem] leading-none text-red-500">40–100</span>
            <span class="mt-2 text-sm font-light text-dark/50">organic per video (~1K with paid support)</span>
          </div>
          <div class="hidden md:flex items-center justify-center px-4"><span class="text-2xl text-dark/20">&rarr;</span></div>
          <div class="flex md:hidden items-center justify-center py-2"><span class="text-2xl text-dark/20">&darr;</span></div>
          <div class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center py-10 px-8 text-center bg-purple-500/4">
            <span class="text-[11px] font-medium uppercase tracking-widest text-dark/40 mb-3">One Video</span>
            <span class="count-up font-display text-[4.5rem] leading-none text-purple-600" data-value="80K+">80K+</span>
            <span class="mt-2 text-sm font-light text-dark/50">views (77x outlier)</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="stats-section max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pb-12">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4">
        {[
          { value: '80K+', label: 'Views on One Video' },
          { value: '77x', label: 'Outlier Multiple' },
          { value: '+4K', label: 'Subscribers from One Video' },
          { value: 'Audience', label: 'Now Asking Him to Return' },
        ].map(m => (
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-dark/8 bg-white/60 p-5 text-center">
            <span class="count-up font-display text-3xl text-purple-600" data-value={m.value}>{m.value}</span>
            <p class="mt-1 text-[11px] font-medium uppercase tracking-widest text-dark/45">{m.label}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pb-16">
      <article class="prose-custom">
        <h3>The Situation</h3>
        <p>Jim Coleman hosts a podcast and runs a farm, working to generate revenue from it through content and community. His YouTube channel was averaging 40–100 organic views per video, with paid support boosting some videos to around 1K. Previous content concepts hadn't found their audience. The channel was struggling to break through.</p>

        <h3>The Approach</h3>
        <p>This was a research-first play. I dug deep into Jim's niche to understand what his potential audience actually responded to — not what we assumed they wanted. The data told a clear story: <strong>previous video concepts weren't aligned with what the niche was searching for and engaging with.</strong></p>
        <p>I strategized an entirely new concept built around the insight that Jim's most compelling story — making six figures from a farm without traditional farming — was exactly the kind of "wait, what?" hook that drives YouTube clicks. The video title: <em>"How I Make Six Figures as a Farmer... Without Farming."</em></p>
        <p>This wasn't just a good title. It was a research-backed format shift. New topic angle, new hook structure, new thumbnail strategy. All designed to give the algorithm a completely different signal about who this content was for.</p>

        <h3>The Results</h3>
        <p>The video hit 80,000+ views, a 77x outlier compared to the channel's average. It generated 4,000 new subscribers from a single video. The audience engagement was so strong that after Jim was unable to continue producing content (due to external circumstances, not results), viewers continued requesting his return in the comments.</p>
        <p>This is what happens when you stop making content you think should work and start making content the data says will work.</p>
      </article>

      <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-dark/8">
        <span class="text-sm font-light text-dark/45">Timeline: Single video concept (ongoing Sweet Fish engagement)</span>
        <div class="mt-2 h-1.5 w-full rounded-full bg-dark/6 overflow-hidden">
          <div class="h-full rounded-full bg-gradient-to-r from-primary to-periwinkle" style="width: 15%"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pb-20">
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-dark/8 bg-white/60 p-8 flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-6">
        <div>
          <p class="font-display text-xl text-dark">Want results like this?</p>
          <p class="text-sm font-light text-dark/55 mt-1">Let's talk about building your content engine.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="mailto:dino@mercurysocialmedia.com" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-7 py-3.5 rounded-full bg-primary text-off-white font-medium text-sm hover:bg-primary/90 hover:shadow-xl hover:shadow-primary/40 hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-all duration-200 active:scale-95 whitespace-nowrap">
          Email me &rarr;
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<script>
  function animateCount(el: HTMLElement) {
    const target = el.dataset.value ?? '';
    const hasPlus = target.includes('+');
    const hasM = target.includes('M');
    const hasK = target.includes('K');
    const hasPercent = target.includes('%');
    const hasX = /^\d+(\.\d+)?x$/.test(target.replace('+', ''));
    const clean = target.replace(/[+MKx%,\s]/gi, '').trim();
    if (!/^\d+\.?\d*$/.test(clean)) return;
    const raw = parseFloat(clean);
    if (isNaN(raw)) return;
    const dur = 1800;
    const start = performance.now();
    const fmt = (n: number): string => {
      if (hasM) return (Math.round(n * 10) / 10) + 'M' + (hasPlus ? '+' : '');
      if (hasK) return Math.round(n) + 'K' + (hasPlus ? '+' : '');
      if (hasPercent) return Math.round(n).toLocaleString() + '%';
      if (hasX) return Math.round(n) + 'x';
      return Math.round(n).toLocaleString() + (hasPlus ? '+' : '');
    };
    const tick = (now: number) => {
      const progress = Math.min((now - start) / dur, 1);
      const eased = 1 - Math.pow(1 - progress, 3);
      el.textContent = fmt(eased * raw);
      if (progress < 1) requestAnimationFrame(tick);
      else el.textContent = target;
    };
    el.textContent = fmt(0);
    requestAnimationFrame(tick);
  }
  const obs = new IntersectionObserver(entries => {
    entries.forEach(entry => {
      if (!entry.isIntersecting) return;
      entry.target.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>('.count-up').forEach(animateCount);
      obs.unobserve(entry.target);
    });
  }, { threshold: 0.3 });
  document.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>('.stats-section').forEach(el => obs.observe(el));
</script>

<style>
  .prose-custom h3 { font-family: 'Instrument Serif', serif; font-size: 1.35rem; font-weight: 400; color: var(--dark); margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .prose-custom h3:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  .prose-custom p { font-size: 0.95rem; font-weight: 300; line-height: 1.75; color: rgba(26, 21, 35, 0.65); margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .prose-custom strong { font-weight: 500; color: var(--dark); }
  .prose-custom em { font-style: italic; }
  .prose-custom blockquote { border-left: 3px solid var(--primary); padding: 1rem 1.5rem; margin: 1.5rem 0; background: rgba(107, 92, 231, 0.04); border-radius: 0 0.75rem 0.75rem 0; }
  .prose-custom blockquote p { font-family: 'Instrument Serif', serif; font-size: 1.15rem; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; color: var(--dark); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .prose-custom blockquote cite { font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-size: 0.8rem; color: rgba(26, 21, 35, 0.45); }
</style>
